hip - a baker on board ship out to the West Indies. - Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15953395 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 Did he do other jobs besides the baking?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5452685 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 
Yes, it was all, mainly full time, yes, oh yes, well he - assisted like on this - when we had the cows, he rather liked that you know, and he used to do the two together more or less, right up to the war. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15953395 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 Do you ever remember him being out of work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5452685 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 Out of work? Good Lor' - no fear. I know one - one certain thing that I well remember him saying and telling the vicar of Luton, that's -
 fifty years ago, he said, do you know what he said? Union sir, they'll be the ruination of this country. He's not far out, ay. Remember him saying that well those days Yes.
\par 
