Yes, oh yes, yes, he wrote a little book about his life on a liner, oh he was - he was a proper card. I always remember - shall I read it to you there - this bit - you'll
 laugh - I've got his old - old - I've copied quite a bit of his - some of his writings out really. I well remember, of course you see what with this - on the dairy side and the baking side - of course he was always busy see, always busy, I always remembe
r
 on one occasion - they - they - this is him, one occasion - he was kicked very bad in the side with a horse, yes, his side was black and blue, all colours, mother sent for the doctor. Doctor said, my goodness, he says, you'll have to stop in bed a few da
y
s. Me, he says, stop in bed, don't talk to silly, I' shall be up there milking them cows in the morning. No, you stop in bed. But not he. Oh he said, do you want to kill me? No, he said, I don't. Well - so - mother went down to Devon - for a holiday. And 
