u very near. Since I left your Devon home, far and wide I've had to roam, as you know I went to sea to work in a ship's bakery. I could tell some truthful tales of ocean liners, sharks and whales, storms and tempests, rain and hail, and how the wind blows
 
in a gale. Those sights and scenes in distant climes made me think of happy times that I might have if I worked ashore, so on the sea I roam no more. Then I found job in - oh this is - then I found a job in Wales, worked for a man as hard as nails. I work
