No, oh no, they was all sent out yes, oh yes, yes, 'cos there was a good cobbler down Barry - down Buxton Road, we used to serve him - serve him with bread I mean they were good customers of ours.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15953395 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 Did you always have new clothes or did you ever have second}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10509621\charrsid11272464  }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 hand ones?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5452685 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 No, no, no, new clothes, yes. That was Easter time.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15953395 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 Were you quite well off really do you remember?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5452685 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 Well -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15953395 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 Ever being hard up?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5452685 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 No, no, not - not what you call hard up really, but - it's like everybody else, there's always do with a little bit more.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15953395 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 You don't remember being hard up or hungry?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5452685 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 Oh no. Oh no, no, no. NO. No, we had a good home really.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15953395 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 How was father around the house, did he help with lighting fires and things like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5452685 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 
Well - no, he could do, he wasn't a bad baker he was one - still the man used to come and do that for him quite a bit, he'd usually be there time
 enough for that yes. Oh I mean more or less - whatever happened you know we - we all - sort of - help each other as it were you know, and - always got this - say to him - oh wait a minute, I'll give you a hand with that, you know, and so on like that you
 see, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15953395 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 Did he have much to do with you children, with helping dress and undress you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5452685 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 
Well I don't know about dressing and that, no, no, he was quite a good - quite a good father. He was a - he was a - a big class leader too you know - down he
 was - he always used to go to a - big Methodist chapel there at - down Chapel Street. Yeah, I even go there now Saturday night to a - well the Good Companions, for us old widows and widowers, we have a jig round and a dance and that and a cup of tea.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15953395 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 They're very active in Luton aren't they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5452685 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 
Yes. Yes. I made old Dowling stare, I shouldn't say old Dowling - the Reverend Dowling, he's the - head minister there. There was another thing that stands out in my memory, I shall never forget that if I li
ved to be a thousand, that was brother and I - we - we used to attend that chapel with - you know, we - we - nearly all - any amount of families had like a private pew didn't they you see, oh yes, used to, well we had ours you see. Well - on two occasions
 
- I told Revered Gowling this, I said, could you this happening today 'Cos it's a big chapel you know, and hold well over a thousand people. I said when the Reverend Mark Guy Pierce come to Chapel Street I was still at school. I was still la - brother as 
w
ell, we were both at Dunstable Road School, and I said when - when the Reverend Mark Guy Pierce come here to this chapel, see - I said do you know what happened. I said it wouldn't be allowed today, because I said all aisles and that must be kept clear. B
u
t when Mark Guy Pierce come here to this chapel to preach - I said, every aisle, every seat in the - stacked in the aisle was occupied. And it was estimated there was three to three hundred and fifty people outside that couldn't get in. I said, could you 
s
ee them days coming back again? No, he said, I'm afraid I can't Well I said that was it. And I always remember - Mark Guy Pierce - what tickled me with old Mark Guy Pierce - when the service was going to start Billy Roberts the - caretaker used to come up
 
with a great Bible and a hymn book see and he'd lay it there. Mark Guy Pierce, when he came out - never seen any other minister do it, but of course tickled brother and I to death 'cos we used to have our little Bibles you know, and Mark Guy Pierce, the f
i
rst thing he done was simply to - remove the Bible and the - hymn book, see. And he'd recite it all off, we will take for our first hymn so and so, and he'd recite it all. What tickled us too was - and now for my first lesson I'll take from - oh - the boo
k
 of St John, see, staring at the sixth verse, and there he'd gesticulate it and draw pictures to you, see here was the Bible laying down here. And we were reading it and it was word perfect you know, yes. Then when he took his second lesson, just the same
 
see. Well, we said, by gum he knows his Bible, I'm blowed if he don't, yes. And always remember - on - what seventy-eight now and I was only a schoolboy, we was going to school, I could tell you the text he took. And the Lord God came eating and drinking.
 
Always remember it, yes, marvellous isn't it? You go in here now and you see people going to chapel now tonight and you can - as they come out and you can say excuse me have you been to chapel? Yes. What was the text? Text, don't - blowed if I could tell 
you. Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15953395 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 Your father and mother went with you did they to chapel always?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5452685 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 Oh yes, yes, we always went, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15953395 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 And Carrie?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5452685 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 No, no, she wouldn't go, no, no, more often than not she'd go home you know, go - go home to her mother's at Flams
tead, it was only just a little village just outside of Luton.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15953395 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 On Sundays that would be would it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5452685 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 
Yes, oh yes, Sundays, then of course she'd have her day off and the usual and - so on. Sometimes her mother'd come in to - us or - well I say if it
 was Carrie's half day and - she said, mother wants to do some shopping so she's going to call here for me, see, and then - we'll go down -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15953395 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 It was fairly free and easy then?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5452685 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 Oh yes, yes, oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15953395 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 Did you remember your parents having time to read you stories?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5452685 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 
Oh dad used to tell us a bedtime story. Oh yes, he was pretty good at all kinds of stories such as that. That's - that's three years running with this - with this class, he used to - he used to - have a class down at the - at the c
hapel. And - throughout Methodism, three years running he turned out more local preacher than any circuit in the country. Yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15953395 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 He must have been a good teacher himself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5452685 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15953395 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 Did mother tell you stories or did she leave that to daddy?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5452685 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 Well, no, she - if she had any she'd tell us, yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15953395 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 
Did you have any regular tasks that were yours apart from your found on Saturdays, did you have to clean shoes in the house or anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5452685 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 No. No, oh no. No. No, no, you was - 
used to go out footballing Saturday morning usually with the school, now I used to play for the school. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15953395 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 Did the older children help the little ones and vice versa in your family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5452685 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15953395 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 Were you taught to help each other?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5452685 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 Oh yes, yes, oh yes. Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15953395 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 What about going to bed, what time did you go to bed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5452685 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 Oh - all various times you see, just depends. Mainly early of course 'cos we was early risers you see. Oh yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15953395 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 Did mother put you to bed or did you put yourselves to bed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5452685 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 Well, she would do or we'd put ourselves to bed and that, yes, oh yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15953395 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 What about a bath before you got the bathroom?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5452685 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 Ah - now what happened there, we used to have a biggish - tub like you know, the old fashioned one - hip
 bath wasn't it. You know, you don't see any of them about now, I dare say they'd fetch thousands now if you had one about.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15953395 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 Did you have it in the kitchen then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5452685 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 Yes, yes, mainly or -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15953395 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 Would you have it once a week?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5452685 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 Yes, round about - yes, yes, Friday night, yes, Friday night.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15953395 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 You had a new suit at Easter?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5452685 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 Yes, oh yes, always reckoned to have a new suit at Easter. Yes, oh yes, used to go proudly off to chapel then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15953395 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 Did you all have new clothes then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5452685 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 Yes, always had a - always reckoned to have our rig-outs at Easter, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15953395 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 Lillian too?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5452685 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 Yes, oh yes, yes, mm. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15953395 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 Where did you have your meals at home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5452685 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 Well more or - more in the living room really, the room mainly just a - you know it was quite clo
se then the kitchen was just through. That was the handiest you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15953395 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 What sort of cooker did mother have?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5452685 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 Oh a gas cooker. Yes. Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15953395 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 Did you ever cook anything in the bread oven?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5452685 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 Oh yes, she used to cook stuff there, oh yes, yes, C
hristmas time - people used to bring their turkeys and that and we'd cook them, oh that was a real busy morning, Christmas morning. Oh yes, they'd bring ducks and chickens and - you know - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15953395 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 Father would charge?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5452685 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 Oh yes, yes, yes, a charge, ye
s, yes, we always had a very busy time too on hot cross bun day, we never had any sleep the night before. No, we used to start - start off - oh - what - about perhaps there, half past three in the afternoon, start making buns, we was on the go all night. 
Y
es. And - when - father was looking after 'em and finishing off about the last batch of buns we used to come up, I always remember mother used to oh fry us up some bacon and eggs and - yes, lovely. Yes, not half, and then - well we'd just sit down perhaps
 
only for about an hour, and then - go out and - shut the pony and trap, well I used to have perhaps go - I'd do a little round there on me own like you know really, and - brother and that and - father perhaps, he would too, go out on the main rounds you s
ee and - always remember Dubley and Whites - we used to call there - a big chemists in Luton they were.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15953395 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 They're still there aren't they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5452685 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 Yes, they are, oh but not now, they had about six blinking shops, had the main shop on - on - the Market Hil
l, and where was - Whites lived I think up Westhill Road, lovely home, I always remember every year - used to - get there, cor, get there around about - oh what, half past five, twenty to six in the morning - bang the door, see this is all arranged you kn
o
w, else otherwise we should - bang the door - every year, always the same, open would come the bedroom window, down'd come the string - used to tie the string round the back neck of the bag of buns - and - right oh, and they used to haul them up, yes. Tha
t was old Mr White, the founder of the business really, oh yes. Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15953395 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 Did you have breakfast together normally?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5452685 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 Normally we did, normally we worked it so that we was all home and all together mostly.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15953395 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 What would you have for breakfast?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5452685 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 Oh a job to say now. Well bacon and egg and all that kind of stuff, oh yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15953395 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 Did you have tea to drink?
