Well he'd perhaps have some early birds round there mushrooming and all that you know used to on the hills there, yes. But - we didn't mind it - it drifted round, and I always remember one - on - well - there was one of our customers, a nice old lad 
he was - I remember dad telling him, he said, well look - tell you what to do, he said, if you feel like getting up - 'cos they were talking about the mushrooms, he said, do you like 'em? Oh, he said, I love 'em mate. Well, he said, come up on the old hil
l
 there and help yourself he said, if you can find any you find 'em, see. Really? Yes. How much then? Oh, nothing, you come up and get some. Well - it worked round that he come up, you know, and he used to get quite a lot and he'd give us some you see. And
 
old dad'd say, well go on, no, no, you picked 'em, they're all right. Well look I - I - we - we shan't want - these'll do me lovely these will, I'll leave you the rest and that's then - and that's how we got them many a time. And sometimes I mean then whi
lst dad and that was up there milking I'd go dodging round you know, pick a few, so - we used to have quite a lot up there, on that twenty-seven acres, yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15953395 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 So you had them for breakfast sometimes?
