\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15953395 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 A happy family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5452685 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 Yes. Oh yes, you could term that absolute, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15953395 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 What do you think your parents hoped you'd turn out as, what did they want you to grow up to be?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5452685 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 Well -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15953395 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 What sort of people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5452685 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 Well I don't know. Just follow in their footsteps. 'Cos - you couldn't beat them really.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15953395 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 You had great respect for them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5452685 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15953395 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 What did they think of swearing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5452685 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 
Oh not so much. Oh no. No. I don't know what they'd think of children now that go past if they listened to that. Well of course a lot of that is all - too much of it ani't it really. Yes, too much of it, just a little now and again but there you are.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15953395 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 If you did something wrong how would you be punished?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5452685 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 
Oh I don't know, dad'd just give you a smack, that'd do it. Or mother would come to that really but - had nothing - oh no, nothing terrible really. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15953395 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 Were they very particular about anything special, was there one thing that they didn't like that you weren't to do?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5452685 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 No, I don't think so really. No, I can't recall anything like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15953395 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 Did you mind being punished or did you think you deserved it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5452685 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 Well you think you deserved it really, if you were punished like really, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15953395 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 Do you think father or mother had the biggest influence on you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5452685 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 Well, I can't say really. Father I think really. Yes. But he'd got such a wonderful 
way you know, of - of talking these things you know he had - he'd look at things differently you see, you can - you could sort of reason it out quite - quick - quick as he used to explain it to you you see, oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15953395 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 You had a good teacher obviously?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5452685 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15953395 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 Can you tell me what it would have been like on your birthdays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5452685 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 Oh yes, oh I - we always used to have a bit of a do. Yes. OH yes, rather, yes, yes. Cards and everything, presents and - oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15953395 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 Did you have a party or friends in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5452685 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 Yes, oh yes, very often. Oh yes, not many but - used to yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15953395 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 What about Christmas?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5452685 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 
Yes. - Yes, oh yes, that was so, yes, we used to have quite parties or go out to party or anything, but of course - you was limited then because you see you w
ere early morning you see, you - you couldn't stop about like they would now do, three and four o'clock of the morning. Anything of that, that was - all we used to have to do was go straight home and change and start work. Oh yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15953395 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 Did anybody play any musical instruments?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5452685 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 
Yes, rather. My brother Fed, as I say he was an organist at the old parish church. Yes, when Gostello was there - he was articled to Gostello and then of course there was the Luton Hooe you know, the great mansion up Luton Hooe
 well - he was down there with Gostello and then of course they used to run a - Luton Hooe choir and they used to go up there to - to Sir Julius Werener's place, Luton Hooe, for the morning service. Well of course - they both more or less worked a little 
bit together, so Gostello perhaps'd say to brother, my brother, you know I - you take the service up there, or vice versa, I'll go up to Luton Hooe this morning there and you stop here you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15953395 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 They'd work together?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5452685 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 Oh it didn't matter where we w
ent, wherever we went or any - any outing, anywhere and you went to any hall and any cathedral, you - you'd find me brother Fred, he - he'd be - he was near that blinking music stool as he could be, if he could possibly - get on it he - oh, nothing'd plea
se him more than -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15953395 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 Where did he get it from were your mother and father musical?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5452685 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 
No, nothing outstanding really I don't know but of course he was a good musician, oh yes - he passed several of the exams and - he - as I say, he - he could play tha
t - organ down there at the - the old church. And he also went on - he's been one one or two of the - the - you know, the later organs what do you call them, them in the cinemas and that. And there - there's a big yes, there's a - a - like the organ at th
e Capitol in London there, he's played that. Oh yes. Yes, oh yes. Oh yes, yes, he was good musician was Fred. I used to do a bit of singing, I mean - oh yes, go round some of these Masonic does and sing, yes, used to sing baritone in me young days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15953395 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 Did you sing at home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5452685 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 
Oh yes, we'd have - oh ay, yes, Sunday night I mean - it was the case of where you got neighbours coming and tap - tap at the door and say - no, we used to - yes, we'd have a sing-song many a Sunday night. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15953395 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 Did you play games together as a family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5452685 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 
We have done, oh yes, we have done, all sorts of games and that, yes. Yes, but the old singing there, I used to - go round as I say to quite a lot of these Masonic dinners and that. Used to sing some of the old songs you kno
w, well they're all dead and gone now, that - Shipmates of Mine, Drake Goes West - Three for Jack, When the Sergeant Major's on Parade, remember that one? OH, not half. Yes, oh yes, used to rat - yes, used to rattle them off you know.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15953395 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 Were you great readers in your house, books and newspapers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5452685 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 Fred was, oh he was always reading really, yes, mm. Very studious, so was Lillian too, oh yes, yes, very much
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15953395 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 What about mother and father, did they read much?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5452685 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 Quite a bit. Quite a bit, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15953395 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 Did you have newspapers and magazines in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5452685 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 Oh yes, we used to have the daily paper. Mm. Just to see if the world was still going round.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15953395 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 Do you ever remember a funeral in the family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5452685 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 Funeral? Yes - oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15953395 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 Were you ever taken to one when you were little?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5452685 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 
Oh I can't remember the first funeral I went to, yes, there was an auntie and an uncle - but - that was at Laverstock Green. Because - at Laverstock Green there were - my - mother's father and mother lived there at Lave
rstock Green you see, and - when we broke up from school - for our summer holiday - say we broke up at school on the Friday, on the Sunday - father and mother used to take Fred and I, us two boys - we was only school - kids then - take us over to Laversto
c
k Green. And we was over there for the month, see for - yes, for the month, and then - say we're going to start school on the Monday, they'd come over on the - Sunday for us. And we used to walk from Laverstock Green, we'd walk - oh, perhaps mile - mile -
 
mile and a half down to meet 'em you know. Yes, and then of course when they came up in the trap we got and - rode back and - of course father - when we got back over to - grandfather's place you see he - would always - shut out and un-harness the horse a
nd that and let the horse out in the orchard, give him some food and that. Oh -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15953395 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 Did you like staying with your grandparents?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5452685 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 Oh yes, yes, then - I got an aunt - an - an uncle and aunt, they had - Cosks Bond Farm, which was only just down the Road
, that was a great six hundred and eighty - six hundred and eighty acre farm that was, oh terrific, yes. Used to stay down there too - in between like or run there or - shall I run down to auntie and uncle? Yeah, right - or the auntie and uncle'd come up 
t
o them you know. 'Cos do you know Luton at all, the heart of Luton at all? Well you know Luton, well now - my old grandfather could have bought the whole of George Street for a thousand pound. There you are. Could have done. Pity he didn't. Yes. I can't r
e
member this, I can't remember this but I always remember my grandfather saying in his early days - he said - 'cos he used to come in to Luton Market every Monday brining in straw, bringing plaits you know for the - straw hats and that you see, and he alwa
y
s used to come in either with a pony and trap or the horse and cart. And I remember him saying - in his early days coming down there he said, I used to come down Chapel Lane, which is Chapel Street, hedges both sides of the road, right down to George Stre
e
t, and do you remember where - do you remember where - Boots - the chemist - where they were at the corner of Chapel Street? Well he said, I used to have to stop there and get out the cart and open a field gate to come along George Street. I can't recall 
t
hat field gate but I can remember hedges and that almost like a - I can remember 'em widening George Street three times. Widening it, and it's no width now. I can remember - of course there was just the half way house between Luton and Dunstable, hedges b
oth sides of the road, used to trot along there with a pony and trap when we went off to Asbridge and never meet another thing.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15953395 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 Was it that auntie and uncle that you remember the funeral?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5452685 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 Yes. Yes, oh yes, yes, went to both of their funeral. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15953395 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 What were funerals like in those days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5452685 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 
Well - well of course I don't know, more - I don't know what you'd term it really, oh it was quite good I mean the whole family and that there and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15953395 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 Did they all wear black?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5452685 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 Yes, all - oh yes, definitely then. Good Lor' yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15953395 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 Sometimes children were allowed to see the body when it was laid out, did you ever see that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5452685 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 I saw - remember seeing - my uncle's, yes, they did let me go in to see - they asked me and that, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15953395 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 Were you frightened at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5452685 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 
In a way I was I think you see I had to hold mother's hand I know, I didn't like it really but - of course they - they left it entirely to me like you know and -
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15953395 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 You were curious?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5452685 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 Yes. Oh yes, I've seen a few since of course.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15953395 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 You obviously had a busy time with neighbours and friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5452685 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15953395 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 You went out and saw them quite often?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5452685 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 Oh yes. Yes. Oh yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15953395 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 Did mother take you shopping?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5452685 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 Shopping? Yes - oh yes, been shopping and that with 'em.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15953395 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 Did you ever go out just with father?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5452685 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 Oh yes, plenty of times I've been out with him, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15953395 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 Where would he take you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5452685 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 Oh yes. Well, just depends, we've - gone off out and - now there's another amazing thing with him - I always remember - a
fter we'd got on that - a bit and we went for a holiday - down to Bournemouth, see. Now this is - well of course years - I was only a - more or less a kid, little kid as it were, we went to Bournemouth anyhow - and - where they picked the news up, whether
 
it was the paper or not I don't know but of course you know - Bournemouth aint far from Portsmouth, well of course my old dad being a Naval - man as it were - baker on board ship - it was announced there that the public - the public would be allowed over 
t
his famous war ship. I forget which - war ship it was. I've somehow got an idea it was the Arathusia, but I wouldn't swear to that. It could have been the O'Ryan, that was another big battle ship, but it was one of the leading battleships - of the day, se
e
. So - what about it? So mother says oh no, no, I don't think - no, I shan't - you go, you go and take the two boys you see, they'd like to go doubtless. She said, would we? OH yes, we would, oh come on then, we'll go - we'll go over to Portsmouth and hav
e
 a look. So we went over to Portsmouth, we looked all over this battleship see, and I always remember - my old dad, he was talking to one of the officers of that boat - at the finish, and of course he was saying - having him - telling him to I mean how he
 
was - been abroad out in the West Indies several times as a baker. Oh well you know a bit about it then, he said. Well what do you think of this? He says, oh - marvellous - a wonderful boat. But, he said, I always remember dad saying, but, he said, do you
 
know, he said, I can foresee the day coming when this boat'll be worth tuppence. Won't be worth nothing. Oh, this officer said - how do you make that out? Well, he said, as regards war, it'll be useless. There'll be rockets flying about and things, yes. I
 don't know, it's amazing, yes, I don't know, yes, yes, how - how he - as long -
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15953395 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 He was like H.G. Wells wasn't he?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5452685 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 Yes, well there you are, he was quite right, yes, he said -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15953395 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 Did you have a holiday every year?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5452685 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 He was about right with 
his union - no, oh no, no, a bit of a job, the work things you know, you've got to get somebody to do the job and that for you and - and - was difficult but - we did manage that, only a few days, I know - I know - I know on one oc - oh that was on one occ
a
sion, what was it - talking about the holidays - and - dad went off on his own, you know, said well you go you see, and he - he - all right, he - he'd go, he'd go until - he went on the Saturday - and until the - Friday, next Friday you see. Monday - Mond
ay afternoon he come walking in. See? Whatever's the matter? Oh I can't stick down there idling about doing nothing. I mean well there you are. Oh yes. He was a lad he was really yes. Really.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15953395 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 Were Bank Holidays special?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5452685 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 Oh yes, oh yes, we liked the Bank Holiday because I mean - you see -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15953395 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 That was when you went to Asbridge?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5452685 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 
Yes, that's right, and I mean we used to - hurry up, I mean well of course you baked for two or three days you see and - then of course that did make it a bit easier. Oh yes, we looked forward to any holiday like - like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15953395 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 
Can we talk a bit about what you used to do at the weekend, how would you - have spent a Saturday in those days, when you were still at school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5452685 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 Still at school? Well - I say - well used
 to go footballing in the morning, I used to play for the school - in - oh yes, Saturday morning. Then Saturday afternoon - we used to - bread round, the little bread round up Stockwood Park. You know, yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15953395 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 How about the evenings?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5452685 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 Well the evenings - well we perhaps played at home really and - played with our parents and that, oh yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15953395 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 How about Sundays, what would you do on a Sunday?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5452685 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15953395 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 Did you get up early?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5452685 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 No, no, just about - no, not extra early really. Di
dn't lay in a lot you know just about normal really and - some - more often than not I used to go up on the - hills with father you see, 'cos we'd got twenty-seven acres up three then and fifteen cows and - well used to help milk them and that, although I
 was only a boy and - yes, and - we used to bring the milk down and sell it in the shop you see. Oh yes, sell it - and they're all warm, no cooling or anything you know, oh lumme people'd come from - away round you know and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15953395 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 What did you carry it in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5452685 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 
Well a church, had a churn and a little - you know, dairy - barrow, like the old fashioned sort as they used to and - only a small thing really and - it was about a ten gallon churn. But of course we - as I say we - we got real good - well then - we 
more or less - started building a bit of a round on it you see. - Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15953395 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 Would you have gone to Sunday school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5452685 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 Yes, used to go to Sunday school, pray yes, oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15953395 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 In the morning would that be?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5452685 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 Yes, in the afternoons we used to go, yes, yes, brother and I.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15953395 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 Did you have a big Sunday dinner?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5452685 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 Oh pray, yes, sometimes too much. Oh yes, yes, that was the - old English dinner you know, the Yorkshire pudding. Oh pray yes, yes.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15953395 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 Would mother cook that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5452685 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 Yes. Oh yes, yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15953395 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 I suppose you put your best clothes on did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5452685 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 
Oh yes. Oh yes, yes. And then - in the evening we'd go to chapel supposed to do, yes, the Wesleyan chapel. We had a pew there you know, like people used to in those days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15953395 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 A family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5452685 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 Yes, l
ike a family pew you see. Oh yes, we was brought up in it, as I say, father was a class leader, see - three years running he turned out more local preachers than any circuit in Britain, yes. Mm.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15953395 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 Were you allowed to play games on a Sunday, were your parents strict about that or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5452685 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 
They weren't all that strict, no, we mainly played and sang you know, with old Fred my brother of course he was organist at - where - I mean - those days we used to have a little family sing-song round the - round the
 - piano Sunday nights you see. Yes, but of course those were the days but - those days gone. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15953395 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 Which chapel was it you attended?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5452685 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 The Wesleyan, in Chapel Street, yes. I - I even go there now Saturday night - no - there's a - there's a Good Co
mpanions - Good Companions club started really and - it's an amazing thing though - the chap that founded that, there was he and his wife, and it was for widows and widowers, and - they started - they started actually in their front room. Yes. And then - 
i
t got - a little bigger and a little bigger until - somebody said, well look, I've got a bigger home than yours, we'll have it in my front room now, and they filled that one up and now of course - they hold it in the - in the large hall - at the chapel. A
nything up to about - eighty - eighty-two. Last Saturday there were seventy eight there, well of course it was a vile day too, last Saturday, shocking weather, yes. Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15953395 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 Can you remember Sunday school outings?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5452685 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 Oh yes, oh pray, used to have the Lut
on Red Cross band - yes, lead the way and we used to go over to Ayot - Ayot. Out Ayot - we used to go be train. Oh yes, and then get off at Ayot Station.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15953395 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 How many children would go?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5452685 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 Oh pray, anything up to - two hundred or more, yes, yes, oh yes
. And - it was gorgeous over there, we always went into the same great huge field one of the farms over there used to let us have this field and - you know - the kiddies all around playing, we played cricket and everything else, we had a darned good tea a
nd then sometimes - after the tea they'd announce what time we'd got to be - all ready you know to go back and - they'd got lovely woods and that Ayat, and we used to go all through the woods, isn't that lovely, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15953395 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 Would that have been about once a year?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5452685 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 Yes, yes, once a year school treat, yes, mm.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15953395 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 What other social activities were there then organized by the chapel, did they have a youth club or anything or a temperance society?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5452685 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 Well - yes, they did have - several, - sort of things for the various ages you know, yes, oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15953395 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 Did you go to them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5452685 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 I used to go always to - father's - you know, his - class when he held his class. Yes. Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15953395 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 Was there a temperance club, are the Wesleyans temperance, very hot on temperance?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5452685 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 
Well they were quite a bit, yes, yes. I know every what - insurances and that in those days I used to have - there was always a cheaper premium if it was tenpence. Yes, well of course we always had those, well we never - never bothered a lot about drin
k. I mean don't even bother now I mean - I'm not a great -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15953395 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 Father wasn't temperance?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5452685 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 
No, oh yes, he never drank at all - plenty of tea but - but I mean really, well you see as things are today I mean I'd have a cup of tea as a lot of this drink.
 I don't say no to a shanty or anything like that but - if I go out to a dinner, now - we've got a dinner coming off, Dunstable Road Old Boys on February the 28th and that's the finest evening in Luton in the year. Anybody that attends it'll tell you the 
s
ame thing, see. We have a - we have the same cabaret show down from London, that costs us about seventeen guineas, the cabaret show. And then we have the good dinner and - well of course you know what dinners are, plenty of wine and everything, and a glas
s of shanty and a - half - half a glass of shanty'll do me, I don't want no more all the evening.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15953395 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 Did you say grace at mealtimes at home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5452685 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 Yes, father used to, yes, yes, sometimes mother too, yes, mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15953395 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 How about prayers at night?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5452685 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 Yes, they was always - always like that, I mean I often think back you know that -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15953395 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 Did you say family prayers together?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5452685 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 Yes, yes, oh yes, yes, yes, oh yes, yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15953395 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 Was your father interested in politics?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5452685 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 Well of course many years ago he was a 
real Liberal. Like the old real staunch old - one of the real old fashioned Liberals. And then he left them and drifted over because - well of course coming along - he often used to say, I mean he'd got no - got no - got no words for unions at all. I know
 
it - I - well remember, and I - I still say - him telling the vicar of Luton, that's anything up to forty-eight to fifty years ago - and I remember him well, they was chatting, and my old dad he says to the vicar of Luton, well sir, he said, unions in my 
opinion they'll be the curse of this country. And he's not far out either. No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15953395 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 Did mother have any political views?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5452685 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 No, Liberal like really, yes, oh yes, she didn't bother a lot about politics, no, not a lot, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15953395 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 Did father do any work for the Liberals, did he go canvassing at elections?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5452685 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 Oh he would do if - yes, but of course he was pretty busy chap you know, he hadn't got a lot of spare time but -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15953395 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 Do you remember them voting at a general election?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5452685 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 Oh yes, they always voted Liberal like that, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15953395 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 Do you remember any particular one, any year?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5452685 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 
Any particular - no, not that I know of, I know who was - MP that days, that was T Gale Ashton. That was his name, yes, forget where he come from, up Nottingham way somewhere.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15953395 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 He was a Liberal was he?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5452685 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 He was the member - member for Luton he was, yes, T. Gale Ashton, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15953395 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 Do you think that it was a fact in those times that people used to vote what their employers voted?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5452685 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 Well I don't know - quite possibly
 quite a few did you know but - oh I don't know - my old dad wouldn't - he - he'd go by his own views he would.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15953395 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 What about people who worked for him?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5452685 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 Yes. Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15953395 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 He wouldn't care what they voted?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5452685 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 Oh no, no, he - he - he'd out and say I
 mean - how he was going on and what he would do and what he was thinking was the best for things and - well left it up to the others if they wanted to vote and there it is. Oh yes, he -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15953395 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 Did they belong to any political club or anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5452685 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 No, no, no, never belonged to a club, no. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15953395 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 When they were not working, I know they worked very hard.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5452685 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15953395 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 Apart from work and the chapel did they have any other interests?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5452685 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 Well -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15953395 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 Any hobbies or anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5452685 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 I can't think really of
 anything, no. No, not really. Other than that I mean he used to - get in his old armchair and put his feet up and - cor this is lovely, he'd say.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15953395 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 Did mother have any interests outside the home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5452685 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 Yes. No, she was always more or less - sort of - b
usy in herself. I mean a lot of people - more or less as I see it those days - they'd have relaxation in doing little odd jobs, you see, yes. I mean you could - you could truthfully turn round and say I mean that - like mother or anything, well I've got a
 few minutes to spare, I know what I'll do, I'll do a bit of sewing or a bit of - oh she was very fond of crocheting, she used to do a lot of that, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15953395 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 Did she have any special woman friends that she went out with, shopping or anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5452685 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 Well she'd got several friends and that - yes, they would do so, oh yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15953395 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 Did they ever go out in the evening together and leave you children with the maid or anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5452685 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 Yes, but not - not generally speaking you know, they were glad of a rest really. Yes. Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15953395 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 They didn't go to clubs or pubs did they?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5452685 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 No. Pray no fear, no, oh no, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15953395 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 Was father interested in sport at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5452685 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 No. He was - after - quite - no, not at all really until - until he come up almost on retirement and I can re
 - in the position where he could take things easier and then - I know my - I well remember mother - saying - do you know, I think we're in for a real hard winter. I said, oh, how's that? Well she says, your father went to the football match Saturday. Yes
. Yes, and - I - I think he really enjoyed it because he used to go quite a lot then, yes, nearly every Saturday then he would but of course when he was in business and that never thought of it, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15953395 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 How about racing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5452685 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 Races, no, no, no, never bothered about that, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15953395 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 He didn't have a bet or anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5452685 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 No, good Lor' no, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15953395 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 Do you remember them belonging to any kind of savings clubs, people used to in those days for sickness or funeral or even shoes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5452685 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 Yes. No, I don't think they - they done anything like that really. No, don't think so.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15953395 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 What about before you left school how did you get on with your brothers and sister?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5452685 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 Oh, very well, very well, yes, oh yes, very well, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15953395 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 Was there any one that you felt particularly close to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5452685 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 
No - well the younger one perhaps - you know, like - you would be perhaps - slightly more but no in the usual way OK we were. That's the one in Canada now, Frank, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15953395 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 He was nearest to you I suppose?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5452685 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 Yes, yes, yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15953395 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 Who did you play with when you were little, did you play with your brothers and sister and with neighbours children?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5452685 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 Well we used to play - no, neighbours and that really. Yes, because -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15953395 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 Where would you play?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5452685 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 Oh out in the street there re
ally, 'course where we were on the - where we was on the - where our shop was on the corner - it was actually the corner - of - one, two, three, four, five roads, all run in, and there was a huge big lamp standard right in the centre. Well we used to play
 
this hare and hounds and hide and seek and all the rest of it there you know and - of course - the main standard - the lamp standard was - was like a - well what would you term it - a - well if you went - if you went - played hide and seek, you know, then
 you found anybody you'd race back and whoever tagged the - tagged the lamp first see, oh well - that was it you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15953395 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 Back to base was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5452685 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 Oh yes, that's right, yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15953395 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 Were you - was your mother very cross if you got very dirty or didn't she mind?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5452685 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 
Oh no, she didn't like that. No, oh no, no, no, no, she'd just go on you know but I mean she wouldn't hit us or anything of that like you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15953395 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 Were you free to play with anybody you chose or was she particular about who she played with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5452685 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 
Well - no, I mean - no, she was - wasn't all that - particular in that way. She might pass a remark, well I shouldn't have a lot to do with them, you know, and that - of course I mean - being in business and that I mean they soon got to know the c
haracter of a good many people you see and I suppose of course that's what they would think. Just the same now, I mean, in - it's funny thing but - as I was in business you see. Mrs Needham - that's our old schoolmaster's wife, I used to serve them, and -
 
they're big church people. This was when - Reverend Davidson was - was the vicar of Luton. And - I happened to - say to Mrs Needham - of course I've been chatting with your vicar. A - a lovely chap, he was a grand man was the Reverend Davidson. And I said
 
to Davidson, I said, do you know, I said, there's character in a milk bottle? Because I was in the dairy trade. Character in a milk bottle, he said Yes, I said, character in a milk bottle. Yes. He said, however do you mean? Well I said look, I do somewher
e
 about three hundred calls a day. Now I said, by the regularity and the state of the bottle - that is put out for me to collect, I could tell you what the interior of the home's like, I said, there's no need to go inside at all. Now I said there's one per
s
on - there's one couple, they're married, they're both out at work - I only see 'em Sunday mornings. They pay me. They've gone to work other mornings. I single their bottle out on one side. And when I've got home I says to the wife, look at that bottle, l
o
ok. How the policemen do they get that as clean as that. Look at it, perfect see. Yes. Well there's no need to go inside that home. You know what it is, I know what it is Sunday morning when I go in you know. Absolutely spick and span, now - next door I s
e
rve next door see. I've got to go on me hands and knees nearly to get any bottles back. Oh they're round by the dustbin. And I go round by the dustbin and there's three bottles or some of 'em see, not even rinsed out. Only just tipped the - tipped the mil
k
 out and thrown them outside, and they'd got two sons - they'd got two sons - over thirt - thirty years of age both out of - both out of work, out of work and on the dole see, that was that family. But they couldn't put a bottle out you see. Well I wouldn
't want to go in there and have a cup of tea.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15953395 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 Were there many rough people round your area when you were a child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5452685 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 Rough - there were - several really dotted here and there you know, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15953395 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 Were they disapproved of by the rest?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5452685 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 Well yes, 
yes, a lot of the other kiddies you know, oh no, aint going to play with them, no, no, won't have them in here, no, no, no, we won't play with those but - but in the general way they was all pretty good really.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15953395 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 Did you belong to any sort of youth club?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5452685 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 
No, no, not them days. Well I would say, just finishing that, I would say that - oh I think it was about six weeks after, I happened to go to Mrs Needham, and - to leave their milk and she tapped the window from inside and - just beckoned me, this 
was on the Monday, see. And she came hurriedly to the door and she said, what do you think Mr Broomfield, the vicar of Luton preached on your milk bottles yesterday. I says, no. She said, he did. Yes. Yes. I thought that was good. Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15953395 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 When you were still at school did you have any hobbies, collect anything or have pets?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5452685 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 
Yes, I used to have a rabbit or two you know for - for a little while, not a lot but I was quite - I was quite interested more or less in woodwork, you know, I used to make little
 things and that, oh yes, I've made things in the home really, a table and all stuff like - that little table, I made that. And - no, I was quite interested really - in - more in woodwork than - anything really, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15953395 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 Did you do any gardening?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5452685 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 Gardening, no we had no garden not in those business premises no. We had no -
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15953395 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 Did you have an allotment at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5452685 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 No. No, never had an allotment, no. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15953395 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 Did you go fishing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5452685 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15953395 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 Did you have a bike?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5452685 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 Oh yes, had a bike, oh 
crikey, yes, oh - oh - the year after I left school, that was the year after I left school - my cousin - I got - there was the three brothers, one was in the Navy, Frank was in the Navy. Horace and Jim, they lived at - Kings Langley. Well we fixed up - an
d we said - we'll go down and see Jim. Is that all right? Yes, so - what about it, shall we go down and have a few days, and - we were going down - on the Sunday. On our cycles, down to Portsmouth, yes. And that was the year -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15953395 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 Just for the day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5452685 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 O
h no, no, Lor' no, no, we - we'd arranged and we was coming back on the Thursday. So anyhow I started off early, on the Sunday morning, had a early breakfast and off I went and - got over to Kings Langley and there we had quite an early dinner like really
.
 And there we set off, there's - Horace, Jim and I. Cheerio auntie, and off we went you know. I'd rather you be doing it than us - me anyhow, so anyhow off we goes. Well - we got - we got down - under - under the clock - tower - oh under the clock at - Wh
a
t - Portsmouth Town Hall just as it's chiming midnight. God bless my soul, we made our way over to the - over to the docks there, and there was a - two nice chaps - was like on duty there at the gate and - this was HMS Nester, and - should be in you see a
nd - we enquired and - it ain\rquote 
t in yet, I'm sure it's not in. Wait a minute we'll make sure, and he got on the phone and rung through. No, it wouldn't be berthed - it wouldn't be berthed until tomorrow - tomorrow between two and four o'clock that would be h
ere. Said, oh bless my soul, what are we going to do now then, see, 'cos - this - the - this brother, he - he'd fixed all up for us and everything see, 'cos he - he was - he was coming in on leave you see and of course was going to be with us and take us 
a
round and this that and the other. And - so anyhow - we left the gate there and we said well we shall have to see what we can do and we walked the old bikes along I know and - there was a - oh what do they call it - a seaman's home, seaman's home, like a 
- a - well no, more like a big caf\'e9
, open all night and all day you know and I know we went in there and oh I don't know we had - fried bacon and eggs and one thing and another. And as we came out, always remember, there was a little old chap there you coul
d hardly see his face for a beard, he had a great beard and a moustache but - he looked - but it's a funny thing but there was one of these class leaders at the chapel here at Luton - he looked like his brother, he did really, yes. And - he spoke to us an
d
 that and - we told him then who we were. Oh dear oh dear, well he said - well boys I've got a spare room, I know - I don't know whether the wife'd do anything, come along with me and see and we went down this little road - it was either Buckingham Road o
r
 Buckingham Place, I know it was Buckingham, anyhow we went down and a little bend in this road, we went just round the bend, Downes this chap's name was. And he - went in and - of course his wife came out, she was a lovely person too really and - oh Lor 
-
 well, you know, I'll see - well you can sleep - have you had anything to eat? Yes, we said, oh we've - yes. So - yes, oh do - can you manage in one room? I've got a - I've got a - a big double bed and I've got a single bed in one room, I'll soon put that
 
all right for you, yes, we stayed there you see and - 'course she give us a darned good breakfast in the morning and that and - yes, and - dinner as well she gave us, yes, 'course we paid her like for it and - and - then we set off - we set off - off to t
h
e docks you see, and - there was two other chaps on duty there - then, of course I suppose they were the day shift like that was on then and - told them how we'd come in, they told us, no, he said, well right, half a minute, no - I'll phone - I'll soon ph
o
ne through and see and - no, he said, it's not in but it'll be in within half an hour. Be in within half an hour. And - he showed us exactly then whereabouts it'd come in. You go up through here and then - and then when - when you get up there you enquire
 and you'll find out where it is, and we see it come in actually, yes. There was -
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15953395 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 So all was well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5452685 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 
Yes, oh yes, there was the - me - me cousin on board there and he took us all over it, all over this destroyer, you know, the - in the destroyer 
in the - oh yes, it was - very interesting. No, and then we stayed there and - all what - over in the Isle of Wight and that and oh we had quite a nice few days holiday, but of course lumme the next morning when we come out I was as stiff as a board.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15953395 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 How far would it be then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5452685 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 Oh - good way. Lumme - oh we had some laughs though when we was only young, just left school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15953395 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 You said you played football, did you do anything else in the sporting line?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5452685 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 Cricket I used to play in the summer, yes,
 oh yes, yes, after I had left school I used to play cricket, I played for Luton Town - wonderful teams.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15953395 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 Did you go to any theatres or concerts or music halls?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5452685 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 Not a lot, no, not a lot, no, not a lot, no. No, I have done more or less lat - latter years, but not - not those days, no. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15953395 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 Would your parents have gone?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5452685 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 No, no, they'd never go, not to - theatres and that like that, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15953395 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 Did your parents give you any pocket money?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5452685 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 Oh yes, they gave us pocket money, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15953395 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 Can you remember how much it was?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5452685 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 Oh - not a lot. Oh pray, no, not like they are today with about eight or nine quid.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15953395 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 You earned a little bit on the bread round when you were little I suppose?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5452685 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 Oh yes, oh yes, father used to pay me something fo
r that, oh yes, yes, I used to bank that like and put it in the Post - oh yes a lit - quite a bit of it, I didn't spend it on such a terrible lot of stuff.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15953395 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 What did you spend money on?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5452685 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 Oh sweets mainly if anything really but - yes, not a lot.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15953395 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 If mother was ill at home, you had this girl living in didn't you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5452685 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 Yes, yes, yes, Carrie, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15953395 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 Did neighbours or friends come in and help at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5452685 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 They would do, oh yes, they would do, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15953395 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 They were very neighbourly were they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5452685 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 
Yes, oh yes, quite good, yes, well I mean - she'd make friends with anybody. Yes. Oh pray, yes. And - I don't know, she'd got a real good sense really of anybody's character she could - she could more or less weigh anybody up straight away even you know 
- a stranger, well - see that fellow in there, I wouldn't trust them a lot, no I wouldn't. Oh dad'd say, you might be wrong. Well I may be but - yes and then usually something turned up - what did I tell you, yes. Oh yes, yes, oh yes, yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15953395 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 Do you remember at all when your younger brother was born?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5452685 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 Younger brother. Yes. No, there's about - what was it, about four years I think. Three or four years.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15953395 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 Do you remember him being born?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5452685 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 Well - faintly really.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15953395 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 Was he born at home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5452685 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 Yes, oh yes, we was all born at home, yes. Sister too, I remember that more so, yes, well she was younger still.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15953395 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 Can you remember what went on?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5452685 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 Well, not really, oh no, I mean -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15953395 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 Did anybody come to stay to help?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5452685 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 Yes, somebody did 
when - when sister was born, I know. That was - oh who was it come then? And auntie from - Laverstock Green. Yes. She came over I know for some - some - well quite a - little while really, yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15953395 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 Do you remember seeing the new baby?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5452685 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15953395 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 What did you think of it, do you remember?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5452685 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 Yes. Oh yes, oh well like kiddies do you know, oh yes, wonderful, oh yes, yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15953395 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 Did you have quite a lot of relations living around?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5452685 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 Yes, we did have relations around, oh yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15953395 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 Did you see them often?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5452685 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 
Quite a bit really. The - the main ones of course was - mother's - father and mother you see, just living at Leverstock Green, near Hemel Hempstead. But I said, I believe you I told you didn't I how we were going over there fo
r the summer's holiday really, yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15953395 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 And your parents had friends I expect?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5452685 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 Oh yes. Yes, yes. Yes. Mm.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15953395 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 Where would they have met them, did they come to the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5452685 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 They have been, oh yes, quite a bit they have done, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15953395 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 Would they be chapel friends or neighbours?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5452685 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 
More or that really or - or - on the religious kind you know, yes. And of course elder brother, he used to bring quite a few really - well singers and all the rest of it you know, oh yes, I mean of course - wel
l according how - that's the vast difference as I say it makes me wild really because - there was two in particular, Bert Puddifoot and - Horace Henley, and - they both had their voices trained and Horace Henley, I always remember him saying that - he rec
k
oned that that cost him about fifteen to sixteen hundred pound when he'd finished, and he finished up number one soloist for Sadler Welles. He was an operatic singer you know. Well - cor he'd got a voice like a clap of thunder, terrici, good Lord yes, he'
d
 - come in some old time you know, any old time, oh Fred, what about it, here run over this number for me will you? Well of course them, him, and so was Bert Puddifoot, they was - they was right on the verge of being professionals you see they were and - 
here, come on, and old Fred'd rattle it off and then - cor -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15953395 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 There was a lot of music in your house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5452685 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 
Yes, but - but of course really that's what makes me wild more or less today when - I'm taking anybody to hospital you know, they say, did you hear the pops on. I say, pops, no blooming fear - I ain\rquote 
t time for them. Then I usually describe it, I said, look in my young days it was a recognized thing that it cost you anything from a thousand - or fifteen, sixteen hundred pound to train a voice proper
ly. Now I says today, and I said they can't hardly get a living too. Now I says, today, I said, you've got to just - just put down a dustbin lid, stand up, kick up an infernal din and as loud a row as you can kick up, see, four thousand a week for you. An
d they say, oh - ay?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15953395 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 But they don't last.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5452685 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 No, but they say to me - are we going to change it. I should think so, cor bless my soul.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15953395 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 Do you remember your mother having any particular friend, did she have a sort of best friend?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5452685 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 Oh I neve
r - oh yes, old nurse - Nurse Burgess, she - yes, there was a Nurse Burgess she did - lived along in the valley, yes, because - we used to - smile - laugh in those days, we used to say, she'd come in and she was happiest of all if anybody was ill. That us
e
d to make my old dad laugh, he says, she's in her element if she can only come and report somebody's - really desperately ill, she's happy as a - yes. One - one great thing you were saying about theatres and that, I always remember - taking mother - I alw
a
ys remember taking mother to - the Palace Theatre in Mill Street the day it was opened. The day it was opened. That's a day or two ago now. And I tell you who come down special from London, Harry Tate - in Motoring. Did you ever see that sketch? Cor, bles
s
 my - it was always billed up, Harry Tate, Motoring and - it was always billed up as - the only show that had the late King Edward crying with laughing for twenty minutes, yes, and it was really, yes. Well my mother - I don't - I don't - I doubt whether m
y mother saw half of the show because she was one of those hearty laugh - cries with laughing you know, look - look - oh and there she was wiping her eyes all the time. I never forget - Harry Tate, Motoring, yes. Oh it was a wonderful bit that was.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15953395 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 Was it a nice theatre?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5452685 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 Oh yes, huge big - it's there now, they have it as a great bingo hall now of course at the Palace theatre, yes, in Mill Street.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15953395 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 It was lovely when it was new was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5452685 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 Oh smashing, rather, yes. Rather. He was the one tha
t come in and opened it I remember that. And - I'll tell you - and - and another thing, I went - that was just at that time - I can tell you the song he sang. Wherever You are Dear. And do you know who that was? You've heard Dickie Henderson? Well it was 
h
is father. His father. And they tell you now Dickie Henderson's getting on. Yes. Yes. Yes, that was Dickie Henderson's father. That was at the same theatre. Just about that time, I think - I don't know - you know, it hadn't been open long and - and he app
eared there, oh yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15953395 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 Did father have any special friends? That he would go to football with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5452685 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 No, not really, no, mainly used to go down and - used to pick his stand there and there he'd be, yes, oh yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15953395 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 Do you remember friends being invited into the house for meals or a cup of tea?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5452685 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 Well, occasionally, oh yes, could do occasionally and - well like these singers and that, when they came in you know, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15953395 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 Would you have any special occasion when you'd have people in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5452685 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 No, I don't think there's anything real special, no. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15953395 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 Would they have been mother's friends invited in or friends of both of them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5452685 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 Friends of both of 'em really, but more - more or less - wrapped up in the chapel like really you know, oh yes, yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15953395 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 A very close knit chapel society?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5452685 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 They were yes, there was no doubt about that, yes, oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15953395 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 Would friends or neighbours have called in casually for a cup of tea, or were they too busy in the shop I suppose?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5452685 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 Well they were - or 
travellers like - you get like Peak Freans travels - traveller, and McFarland Langs and that, you know, I mean mother would always say, will you have - would you like a cup of tea? Oh rather Mrs Broomfield, yes, well I'll go and make then, she'd go and ma
k
e a cup of tea, or shout through to Carrie, Carrie, make a cup of tea will you. Mr Jones here, he was one of the traveller - who was the - and May he was the other. I forget which one they were. I always remember because - I well remember - as I got on an
d
 that I used to - used to play billiards and that, that's a long while before ever snooker was thought of you see, and - we more or less drifted over then like - as Conservatives, this was at the Conservative Club, I won the cup there oh two or three time
s
 up there, and - there was - Mr Jones, I can't think which - it was one of the biscuit people, it was either Peak Freans or McFarlands, one or the other, but anyhow he happened to - call, he used to call monthly, and - mother always - they always used to 
-
 pay him a cheque like for the month - before like see, and then give him the order for this next months you see, and - I don't know what but - oh he came up and he said, do you know, he said - he said - we was talking, on sport more or less, he said, do 
y
ou know, he said, I'm rather keen on any sport, any sport with a ball in it, I like any sport really with a ball in, he said, I play tennis and that, I've played cricket, I've played football I have done and - but the best of all, he said, I like billiard
s
 best of all really, he said, I sort of specialize a bit more in that than anything. Well, I said, I have a game or two. Cor lumme, he said, well can we have a game you see. So - I said, yes, if you like. I said, I'll tell you what I'll do, next - month, 
w
hen I come here to Luton, he says, I'll hurry up - and I'll hurry up and get on done and try and get done and we'll nip down the club there and have a game shall we? I said, yes, that's OK. Well I hadn't got an earthly chance, you see, no. He was a - hund
r
ed break chap, you know, he could make a hundred break, hundred and ten, hundred and twenty and such like and - oh I said, you're far too good for me and that you know. He said, well I'll tell you now he said, do you know, he said, that's - two years runn
i
ng - I've got knocked out the final of All England - Championships in London. Oh dear, I - yes, still I learnt a lot from him really, oh yes, yes. 'Cos they say really in anything - if you want to improve in anything you always want to play with somebody 
better than yourself, see. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15953395 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 Do you remember society being divided up into different social classes in those days?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5452685 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 What at the -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15953395 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 In general, society, you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5452685 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 Yes. Mm. Well - you could do, yes, I suppose.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15953395 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 How do you remember them, was there an upper class or what did you call them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5452685 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 
No, well - more - more by the age like you know. Perhaps you'd get a - you'd get somebody have a'em all up to so and so age, you see, 'course my father I mean when he was doing this - work - w
ith his class I mean well they would be anything up to thirty years old you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15953395 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 I didn't mean that kind of class.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5452685 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 Oh.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15953395 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 I meant social class, like working class, upper class, middle class?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5452685 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 Oh. No, I don't think there was anything much about that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15953395 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 Do you remember there being an upper class in Luton?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5452685 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 Well Lord - more like the Masonic business, I mean they was all more the aristocrats like weren't they, oh yes, more or less, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15953395 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 What sort of people belonged to that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5452685 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 Well more like - the upper business people, like - like manu - hat manufacturers and all that you see, oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15953395 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 How about doctors?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5452685 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 Well they were all come in the same more or less, yes, oh yes, in that type, yes, oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15953395 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 How about shopkeepers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5452685 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 
Well depends what size your business was really, oh yes, I mean you - say - they would more or less sort of drift in classes I think you'd say that, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15953395 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 What would you have considered your parents were?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5452685 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 Well about in the middle, I'd say, yes, really, yes. Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15953395 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 What sort of people made up the working classes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5452685 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 
Well - the old marketers or - stall holders and all the rest of it, when - yes. 'Cos I mean used to have open markets in the streets and that you see, they used to.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15953395 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 Did people stick very much to their classes do you think?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5452685 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 
I think they did, yes, oh no, oh no, I don't think they - no, I think they used to stick quite in their classes really. Oh yes. Well they do even really today more or less.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15953395 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 Do you think there was a way of getting out, either getting higher up or going down?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5452685 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 Well if they rose up if - if good fortune began to fall on 'em and so on, yes, oh a lot to do with it of course, yes, oh yes, yes. Yes.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15953395 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 What for instance would vicars have been considered, would he have been upper class?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5452685 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 Well - be more so wouldn't he, although in a way really a lot of them were more or less in a class of their own. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15953395 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 Who would they have mixed with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5452685 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 Well I don't know, you don't see any in the \{BLANK\}
 now do you. No. No, I mean you take the Lansdowne Club, well there'd be all directors of firms and that really, all around here, I mean you - like - well anything - well you're talking about their class, all the - all the tip top of the Vauxhall
, see, you'd have them members down there, but you wouldn't have these blooming shop stewards and all that, they're not in it of course - they - pitched them out straight away.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15953395 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 Can you remember if you were brought up to treat people differently, if you were expected to touch your cap?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5452685 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 
Oh used to years ago, oh yes, oh rather - oh yes. Those were the days when, as I - I've said this many a time - Matthew Plummer, I used to serve them, that was on Crescent - up Crescent Rise, real residential area, he was the head manager of J }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15953395 &}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464  C. Kershaw\rquote 
s Limited. That held - that had - a terrific place - all hats and that, used to go all over the world these hats do. Well - Matt Plummer, Matthew Plummer - used to come - out of his place, and he'd walk down, they'
d got a car and that but he used to walk down to business wee with a perfect rolled umbrella, his high silk hat, see, his wing collar, tails see, as I said really, I've said many a time, if he come down the - and he usually - more or less walked - in the 
centre of the road more, with a lovely buttonhole, oh lovely - out of his greenhouse there. I said, if you saw him coming walking down there today, well of course today he'd get stoned he would then today wouldn't he.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15953395 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 Were you told to touch your cap?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5452685 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 
Well we would, always - always used to salute him and that oh yes, same as we used to Sir Francis Crawley when I used to go up Stockwood Park when I used to see him. On the bread round, when I used to do a little bred round up there. Oh yes, people l
ike that and then - there was other real aristocrats really like - along the Downs Road. See, there was a - Doctor Bolton Thomson - a wonderful surgeon lived along there, Harry Arnold the - the - big timer people here. House - the St Gregory's school whic
h
 is now along here, it was only a little tiny school now, but they - he was the founder, Mr House, of - St Gregory's school. Well all them but they - they don't exist in here somehow in Luton now today, up there - I don't think - I've been - went up there
 
about two years ago, about two years ago, would I go up to the Downs Road and pick somebody up from - flat so and so - and take over to Hillend Hospital at St Albans. And I hadn't been up that Downs Road for years and years, you - oh it make you cry, it m
a
ke you cry to go up there. There's all blooming lodging houses and - oh - oh dear, and those - great homes up there and just - every one's got a - a - their own room, you know, you've got to go down this place - oh dear, it - it's - well - put years on yo
u to look at it, and you think oh my, are we in a changing world? And I - in fact I say we are.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15953395 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 Did you have to call people like that sir?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5452685 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15953395 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 And the ladies madam?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5452685 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 Well we used to, oh yes, yes, always used to, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15953395 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 Would poorer people have respected your mother and father in that way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5452685 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 Oh yes. Yes, oh yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15953395 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 They held quite a good position didn't they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5452685 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 Yes. OH yes. Yes. - Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15953395 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 Who were considered the most important people in Luton, would they have been the top businessmen?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5452685 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 Well they would be really, yes. Oh yes, I should say so.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15953395 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 What about the landed gentry?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5452685 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 Mm? Well - you didn't see much of them in Luton really you see, no, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15953395 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 Luton was mostly little firms and hat factories?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5452685 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 Yes. OH yes, yes, big hat - large and small. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15953395 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 Were they considered important because they were rich?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5452685 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 I suppose that'd be more or less it you see, oh yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15953395 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 And they'd give work to the people in the town?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5452685 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 Oh yes, yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15953395 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 What sort of people were your father and mother's friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5452685 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 
Well they were - well they could be business people or - or mainly all to do with hats you know, in the hat trade and that, yes, oh yes, yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15953395 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 What do you think the difference was between people who went to church and those who went to chapel?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5452685 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 Well I don't know, not such a terrible lot really. But of course - well there\rquote 
s church, high church - no, but - yes. Yes. Of course my old dad's religion - I always remember saying - he sai
d - and he - you can't go far wrong - now what was his - what was his - one of his - my religion is to - the one - you know - love - love, mercy isn't it - do justly and walk humbly with the God, what's that one now - he said, if you - if you stick to tha
t you ain\rquote 
t going far wrong you see, and that's how more or less he would talk. Love - no - no what was the other bit before that? Love mercy - walk humbly with they God, I know that. To do justly, love mercy and walk humbly with the God. If you stick to th
at you won't go far - yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15953395 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 Did you ever know people who went to church?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5452685 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 Oh yes, yes, oh yes, we served a lot in the business you see, oh pray yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15953395 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 What sort of people would they have been, did the richer people go to church do you think, or wasn't it to do with that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5452685 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 
Well - possibly it would be I should imagine, yes. Yes, I should imagine really although of course you got plenty of poor people used to go.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15953395 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 Luton was very strong in chapels wasn't it?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5452685 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 It was in chape
ls, oh yes, very - very much so, yes, oh yes, some of the real prominent men of the - of the - town were chapel and so they were of church of course. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15953395 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 What do you think about the standard of living of the really working class people, were they very poor?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5452685 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 Well I think they - not too bad. Not really all that too bad.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15953395 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 Did you have people -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5452685 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 
Because you see so many - so many in Luton I mean if - you could - you term the poorest of the poor really. I mean they could do work at home, they
 could make hats at home. Lot of the big firms then'd bring the raw material and dump it, there you are, right, then - it was up to you, if you like to sit up night and day and make some hats well you make a few pound you see. Oh yes, that's - that's how 
it is - there's quite a few - there's quite a few take in work today you know in Luton, on a -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15953395 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 
Do you think there was a difference between those sort of working people who could make hats which is quite a craft, and real labourers who swept the roads and things like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5452685 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 Well there's a difference between them? Oh yes, really, oh yes, yes, there would be. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15953395 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 Would they consider themselves better?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5452685 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 I suppose they would. OH yes, they would really, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15953395 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 Were there very rough families, I mean really rough that people tried to get rid of?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5452685 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 Oh yes, there were one or two real - staunch characters in Luton.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15953395 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 Do you ever remember any rows and trying to evict families?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5452685 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 Well, yes, I mean always up the police station when they u
sed to arrest these - who was one, Lick - oh was Lick - Licker Sharp they used to call. Yes, Licker Sharp you see, yes, but - he was - he was always drunk, you'd never find him sober, Licker Sharp.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15953395 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 What happened to him?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5452685 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 He used to go out with hats, he used to take hats out, yes, he'd go out in the villages and all round you know and that, yes, oh yes.

\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15953395 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 What about his family, did he have a family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5452685 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 You'd go by with a car and - go on, you - I could have hundreds of you if I - he got - alw
ays remember Licker Sharp one day got - bottle of beer in each pocket, and one in his pocket here - he was going home - you know, it was in George Street, the main Street, he was just going home one evening - couple of women called across to him see. Alwa
ys remember, said, would you like a cup of tea Licker? They used to call him Licker, everybody. Would you like a cup of tea Licker? He looked round, you know, he's half cut, he says, tea, I ain\rquote t tasted it for years. Ain\rquote 
t tasted it for years, he says, here
's my breakfast. And pointed - yes. But - really - I mean - he was - that was his character really, he was more or less all like that, never seemed to get in any trouble and that, oh no. There was one other - no - no - oh there was - there was one - there
 
was one bloke, I don't know what his name was, they used to call him Moonshine. Moonshine, he used to live rough, live out in - in - you know, he was a - well, he - he'd pass out as a blackie really, but very often the old saying was that - the old saying
 
was - he was taken ill one time, they found him laying somewhere ill and they took him up the hospital. They took him up the hospital and bathed him and when they'd bathed him for ten minutes they found he'd got another waistcoat on. Yes. Yes. That was - 
w
hat - old Moonshine, they used to call him Moonshine, you see - but there was a - wonderful old character we used to laugh at too, but he come from away, but he was all right enough but - he'd got a hurdy gurdy you know, an organ. It'd only play about hal
f
 a dozen notes and all the others were blanks, and - yes, we always used to call him Wet Weather you know, yes, I don't know - say hello, old Wet Weather's in Luton again. Yes, I used to say I heard him up such and such a street, yes, oh blimey we're in f
o
r a wet spell. They always called him that, they were - every time he sort of come to Luton it always rained, yes. But I remember too and - on one occasion we went out with a pony and trap about - I believe it was when we went over to - Leverstock Green, 
we was out - Hemel Hempstead, on one occasion? I - bless my soul look here, down the road, look, there was old Wet Weather playing his organ. He used to go from town to town and that. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15953395 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 And would people give him money?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5452685 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 Oh yes, people'd give him a coin or two you know yes. Yes. OH yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15953395 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 Did your mother and father have the same attitude to people in different classes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5452685 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15953395 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 Did they think alike on things like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5452685 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 Oh yes, really they'd got to more or less you know I mean you'v
e got to more or less in business you've got to - I mean if you - if you hated the sight of anybody you can't really go up and tell 'em so, because you don't know where it's going do you, you see, so I mean you've got - you've got in a way to - but old da
d
, he always got a wonderful way of expressing himself, you know, I mean - he'd leave anybody - in - anybody that left him'd know what he meant see, whether they agreed with him or not that's a different thing but - he would just say such things as I've to
ld you like about unions and that you see, he said, they'd be the curse of this country. And nobody ever make him join a union.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15953395 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 Do you remember people being described as a real lady or a real gentleman?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5452685 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 Oh yes, you used to get those, Lady Keynes, oh yes, pray she was quite a big lady in Luton there. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15953395 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 Would they have come to your shop?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5452685 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 
Yes, oh we used to serve Keynes, yes, yes, Lady Keynes, she was a - he was a big lawyer and that really, yes, oh yes, and - she done a wonderful lot 
too - you know, as they got on and - she done a wonderful lot for Luton there, yes, in the hospitals and the opening this and opening that and - fetes of all sorts and that yes, oh yes, quite a big name there. Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15953395 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 Do you ever remember seeing a policeman around when you were a child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5452685 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 Oh pray yes, plenty of coppers around, yes, oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15953395 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 Were you frightened of them?
