I mean they - well got one or two there who I wouldn't trust him, no he'd have you if he could you know, and others I mean - one of the most - one of the - one always sticks out in my memory really was old Inspector Hagley, he was a Devonshire man. Well o
f
 course my man - my father was from Devon see. And - but he was a one you know and - he - come here, come here, you know, and he'd fetch somebody up then - he'd - he'd - he'd give 'em a real dressing down you know, wouldn't hit 'em at all. See, but I mean
 
- I don't know, and - and they'd respect him a lot more, see, yes, yes, oh yes, I've heard somebody - I've heard some of them say to youngsters you know, cor bless me soul - old Inspector Hagley caught us, cor did he dress us down, yes, yes, say did you l
earn anything? Yes, yes, oh he was right. Yes. OH.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15953395 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 Were you ever given lessons by your parents or anybody else before you went to school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5452685 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 No. No, not - I can't recall.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15953395 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 How old were you when you first started school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5452685 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 Oh went to school, 
well, went in the - more or less in the infants it was really. I was - four years old, three - three to four years old that's all, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15953395 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 Did you go for the whole day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5452685 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 Yes, oh yes. Oh yes, yes. Oh yes, there was no easy fists.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15953395 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 What kind of school was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5452685 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 Oh quite nice, yes, we - we enjoyed it, oh yes, quite a big school, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15953395 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 Was it a kind of Board school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5452685 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 Yes, more so, yes, yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15953395 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 Not a private school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5452685 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 No, no, not a private school, oh pray no, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15953395 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 Was it boys and girls mixed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5452685 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 Yes. Mixed, yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15953395 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 How did you get to school?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5452685 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 Yes, used to walk. Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15953395 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 Did you go with your -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5452685 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 No, well once I knew I mean used to run off to school or meet some of the other kiddies and go with them and
 - oh we had no - and - no conveyance call round and so on. We got ten minutes - you got ten yards to go, you'd better ride. There was none of - not them days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15953395 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 How far was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5452685 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 How far? What - oh it'd be about - oh - what would you say - half a mile, three quarters of a mile perhaps, yes, oh not far, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15953395 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 Did you come home for your midday meal?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5452685 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 Yes, used to come home for that, yes, oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15953395 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 What did you have to eat for that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5452685 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 Oh used to have good meals really, yes, all various you know - various - meals.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15953395 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 A cooked meal was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5452685 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 Yes. Oh yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15953395 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 What did you think of school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5452685 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 All right really, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15953395 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 Did you like it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5452685 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 Yes, used to get on quite all right, oh yes. Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15953395 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 How did you feel about the teachers, were there some you liked better than others?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5452685 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 Well yes, they was - well there were some good teachers.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15953395 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 What was your teacher like when you started?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5452685 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 Well - well very good, that was a - lady teacher then, right at the beginning, 
I know - Berth - Bertha Green. Yes. Then there was a - then we had a - a man teacher, Sylvester, there was Freddie Carter, there was - Sammy Pride. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15953395 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 Would Bertha Green have taught you everything, you stayed with her for a year?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5452685 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 Yes. Yes. Yes. Yes, more so, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15953395 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 And then went up to another teacher?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5452685 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 That's right, you move - move up you know, after an exam you go on up and - from class to class.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15953395 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 What did they consider was important in life, did they mind about manners and tidiness, punctuality?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5452685 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 
Oh yes, the teachers and that did, they used to try and instruct us on that, oh yes, yes, yes. Well Sammy Pride - he died last year, what was he - ninety-four. Ninety-four. Ninety-five, and you know, that's Dunstable Road old boys - 
he was in a home down at Folkestone, and - three years running - we always have a - an outing in the summer, and three years running - running we went down there to Folkestone, and had a tea up there in - a municipal place up on the Lees, you know Folkest
o
ne at all? Oh - lovely, yes, no, well up on the Lees. 'Cos like all the other places you've got the posh end and the - rough end, and it - but it's up the - it was a nice home apparently where he was, you know, he use to have to pay, I don't know what he 
p
aid, quite a lot of money to be there at this home. And - we went there - right up - and I mean now you see - the finest evening in Luton in the year - now is the Dunstable Road old boys, us old boys - dinner and - cabaret show and dance, that's on Februa
r
y the twenty-eighth. So if you want a good evening out you want to come there. Cabaret show costs us about seventy pound. They come down from London, we always have the same cabaret show. Yes, at the halfway House they hold it, do you know the Halfway Hou
se in - along the Dunstable Road. Yes. Finest evening in Bedfordshire in the year. There you are.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15953395 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 If you were naughty at school would you have been punished?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5452685 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 Oh yes, you get the cane, oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15953395 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 Did girls get it as well as boys?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5452685 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 Yes. Yes. Oh yes. Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15953395 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 What sort of thing would they give you the cane for?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5452685 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 
Well - well I don't know, talk - well - disobeying really. Yes, talking in class and suchlike, I mean - we were allowed to at times but if they said no talking, well no talk
ing was no talking. If you did start talking away well there you are, you got the cane. Of course it's not quite so bad - not quite so bad as my old dad when he was at school, I remember he - I can always remember him saying that he only had six months ed
u
cation. That's all, that's all, yes. And - Badger Green was his teacher. Do you know how he used to punish them boys? Used to hang 'em up by their thumbs. Yes. And me old dad says I've seen boys hung up with their thumbs. Yes. Oh we're in a changing world
. Yes. Yes. Yes, he was - yes, yes, he was only at school six months, that's all. Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15953395 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 Did your parents show an interest in your school work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5452685 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 Oh yes. OH yes, yes, oh yes, they was always pleased like you know if we - done well or anything, oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15953395 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 Did they visit the school and talk to the teachers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5452685 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 
Oh yes, they have come down, yes, oh yes, yes, they used to have these - sort of - open day as it were you know and - exhibit - whatever you could do, I used to do a bit of drawing and - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15953395 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 Did the other children come from similar sort of homes as you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5452685 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 Yes, more or less, yes, oh yes, yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15953395 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 Were there any gangs or groups in the school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5452685 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 Well yes, they would gang up a bit you know. Yes, you could get 'em like that really.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15953395 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 Can you remember any particular child they'd gang up against?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5452685 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 
Well it could be, you could always get - funny thing you know but I was only thinking of that, I think it was yesterday really. Now - those olden days, you'd - get somebody come 
along in that school and oh they want to rule the roost. They're the guv'nors see ain\rquote 
t they, you know, it's the other kids they sat on these other kids you see. And I tried to work it out to a degree how things are today, see, a kid must be touched today 
not by anybody see. Now - what would - what used to please you more than anything - oh we've got a new boy coming to the school see, he's come from away, see, or his parents have moved here, come to work at the Vauxhall or something of that you see. And -
 
when this lad then that's always been sort of ruling the roost you know, the big head as you might say see, this other lad might take him down a notch you see. Well of course we always used to like that and see that. And to a degree I think that's how rea
l
ly things - in a way should be today. I was only saying, now - you take this - hooliganism. There's this - blooming - some - Powell ain't he - one - something big to do with the big football world, he reckons the finest thing to stop this hooliganism is t
o
 stop boys from seventeen - up to seventeen years of age from going to a match. Have you ever heard anything so barmy and so daft, well it'd close any amount of grounds But there was one letter, there's ever - ever so many letters in there, and there's on
e
 - said I've got a far simpler way than whatever Howell says - what - whatever Howell says, and that is for the real hooligan, give him the birch and fine him as well. And I thought now that's - that's the most sensible blooming letter of the whole issue 
that is.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15953395 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 Do you remember the teachers having favourites in the class?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5452685 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 Oh yes, they could do, yes, oh yes, they sort of -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15953395 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 What would their favourites be?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5452685 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 Well, those that were getting on the best I suppose more or less in the class, yes, really, but -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15953395 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 Did you go on to another school after that one?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5452685 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 No, I was only at Dunstable Road, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15953395 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 What age did you leave there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5452685 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 Oh what was it - fourteen - was it - four - about fourteen.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15953395 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 Would you have stayed longer if you could? Or had you had enough of school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5452685 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 Well I'd had enough of school really I mean - I - I reckon I was - learnt a lot there since - since I left school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15953395 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 You don't have any regrets?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5452685 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 No. No, no, no, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15953395 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 When you left school, your first full time job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5452685 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 
When I left school, well - ah - was in the bake-ring you see right up until the war, then we went in the war see, brother - elder brother he went in the Navy, I went in the Army.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15953395 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 Do you remember what sort of hours you worked?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5452685 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 Well - we worked 'til we - well yes, we worked 'til we finished the job you see. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15953395 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 Did you ever have a half day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5452685 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 Half days - well, yes, we can work it so that - yes, it could be so, like a - perhaps brother and I'd more or less take turns
, you know, and then - he wanted to go out and anything like that, well I - I'd do the other extra bit you see.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15953395 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 Do you remember how much you were paid?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5452685 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 No, I can't remember really, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15953395 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 Did you think it was a fair wage at the time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5452685 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 Oh yes. Yes. Oh yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15953395 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 You thought father paid you enough?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5452685 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15953395 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 Did you give any money to your mother for your keep?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5452685 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 No. No, that was all more or - less separated out like how we done it you see and then - they'd say well look we'
ll give you this - pocket money to keep you kind so on you see, like that, no. No, was no complaints that way really.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15953395 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 How did you get on with the other people you worked with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5452685 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 Well -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15953395 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 You'd known them all your lives anyway hadn't you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5452685 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 Yes, oh yes, yes, used to get on quite all right with them. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15953395 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 Did you ever resent working for your father at all or was he a good employer?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5452685 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 Oh no, no, oh no, quite - no, no, no, no, he was quite good, oh yes, quite good yes. Oh yes. Yes, oh y
es, got no complaints like that anyway.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15953395 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 Did you ever think you'd rather have done something else or were you quite happy doing that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5452685 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 No, I was happy enough doing that really, yes, oh yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15953395 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 Did you ever belong to a trade union at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5452685 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 No blooming fear, no. Heavens above, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15953395 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 Any professional organisations?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5452685 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 
I should like to - I should like to see some of these blooming officials of the trade unions do a damned days work. Ay? They don't know what it is.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15953395 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 Were there any professional organisations in those days, tradesmen\rquote s organisation of any sort, like the Rotary there is now?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5452685 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 Oh yes - yes, there was like - there's association, Bakers Association and that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15953395 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 Did your father belong to that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5452685 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15953395 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 And you did too did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5452685 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 
Yes, oh yes, father and that did and - oh yes, we used to have like the - the regular outings, summer outing you know, used to go over to - Mentmore Towers, there, we used to go over there say with the old brakes, wagonettes and that you know, yes. Yes.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15953395 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 Did you feel there was a division in those days between craftsmen and ordinary workers, your baking would have been a craft wouldn't it?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5452685 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 Yes. Oh yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15953395 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 Would there have been a difference between a man who had a skill and a man who didn't?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5452685 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 Yes. Yes. Oh yes, there was a difference yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15953395 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 Did you look down on a chap?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5452685 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 No, no, not really because I mean - they - well like now you take Luton, well I mean Rudd's more or less - went ahead with all the - th
e - more the fancy stuff in the - in the baking trade. All the confectionary. I mean Rudd sent his - both his sons - father sent my brother up to - London Polytechnic. Oh yes, see the - the - yes, to learn the better class of the trade you see. But who wa
s it used to - they were the best business of the whole - Luton then, Rudd's. They'd got two or three shops, they had one in Dunstable Road and one in Church street and - so on, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15953395 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 Would you say that full time work changed your general attitude to li
fe when you left school, did you feel any different about things, did you feel grown up straight away?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5452685 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 
Well - yes, felt more - you know, you was responsible for more stuff - yes, like that because - well I mean you - we set out on our own, we used to
 do our own rounds and that you see and - well like in a way you was more or less your own governor as it were see. Oh yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15953395 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 You continued to live at home, how long did you live at home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5452685 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 Oh Lor' - right up 'til the war.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15953395 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 When did you get married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5452685 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 During the war, 19 - 16. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15953395 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 It must have been rather difficult for your father to stop treating you as a child when you left school wasn't it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5452685 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 Oh - no, we sort of - gradually went along like, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15953395 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 It was quite easy was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5452685 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 Oh yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15953395 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 You carried on going to chapel?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5452685 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 Yes, oh yes, I did that, yes, oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15953395 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 Did you take an interest in politics?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5452685 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 Not a lot, I sometimes used to go to some of the meetings and that and - yes, I - one meeting especially - tha
t was a - we was more or less Liberals then but I always remember in the old - in the old Plait Hall - a meeting there - with - who was it came, well two different meetings, I think they were two different elections, old Lady Aster was one, Nancy Aster, t
he most }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10505068\charrsid11272464 fieriest}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 
 woman speaker I've ever heard in me life, never heard anything to touch it. Cor lumme. But this other meeting was - was - old - F.E. Smith. Do you remember F.E. Smith?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15953395 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 There was F.E. Smith?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5452685 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 Oh yes, F.E, - in the Plait Hall - F.E.
 Smith that became Lord Birkenhead, and old - Sir Edward Carrs. There was a rare sing-song because they was a bit late getting there, and old Hugh Cumberland, that's the big auctioneers at Luton, they was - he was in the chair. Well - in the market hall t
hose days it was always on a Monday, the cattle market and that, well - was a - chap there that used to come - used to come out from the office rin}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10505068\charrsid11272464 g}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 ing a bell, like the old town crier would you know, and he'd ring the bell - for whatever was going to be sol
d, it was always reckoned say at half past one to sell the poultry. Two o'clock it was always the pigs, you see. Eleven o'clock in the morning was the beef. And he'd come round with the old bell, all these farmers from all around'd meet and they're chatti
n
g away and the bell'd go, hello, listen, here we are, we're ready to sell the beasts, then they'll all go up to the centre see and - where it was all put up for auction you see, how much for this and the rest of it see, then the old bell'd go about half p
a
st one for the poultry. Two o'clock it'd go for the pigs see. Well - and - and old Anthony - there was Anthony and Hugh Cumberland, the two brothers. One'd sell one thing and one the other you see. And - as I say they were the big - big - market people of
 
this town. Well - Hugh Cumberland, he was Chairman at this meeting you see. Well - to quell it all down, hammering and stamping you know for everybody, you know, silence please, silence, you see, 'cos he was going to announce olf F.E. Smith to speak you s
e
e. And he got all this silence see, I shall never forget it, got this dead silence, you could have heard a pin drop you know, just then - when old Anthony - Hugh Cumberland - he just - got his little hammer there, he was - he was just going to - just goin
g
 to start - and a voice, one of the old drovers, one of the drovers, he used to drive the cattle and that - right in the back of the hall, he shouted up in all this silence, now for the pigs. Oh. Everybody roared. Yes. Yes, then he called on old F.E. Smit
h
 then. Yes, always remember F.E. Smith, oh he was a fiery speaker was F.E. Smith, there was one - there was two things, now whatever was it? 'Course it - it's no use heckling them chaps up you know, they've got answer for you whether they're right or whet
h
er they're wrong, they have - well always remember there was - somebody shouted something out to old F.E. Smith. And old F.E. Smith - oh, old F.E. Smith, he shouted back - oh, he said, the man that shouted that out, he said, his head's only fit to hang hi
s
 hat on. Then he goes on with his speech you know. OH yes. And then a bit afterwards I can always remember - and I thought that chap was rather smart because - old F.E. Smith was all on - all on the - the figures of the country, you know - all - what the 
-
 prices of everything and running into millions of money you know and somebody shouted - heckled something up at him you know. And he stopped instantly and he looked round, he said, the man that shouted that out, he said, he's a donkey. And this bolek, I 
t
hought that was rather quick, because he shouted back, he said, well there's two - there's two of us. Old F.E. Smith turned straight round, he said, yes, he said, my brother he said, do you know, he said, I've been listening very very intently to your - b
ray for the last ten minutes, but I'm hanged if I can see your brother. Yes. Ay? Oh that was smart. Ay? Oh yes, you can't beat them chaps.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15953395 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 Did you carry on doing the same things in your spare time once you'd started work full time? Did you go out in the evening at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5452685 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 Yes, sometimes, oh yes, sometimes we'd go out, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15953395 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 Where would you go?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5452685 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 Oh - mainly walks and that really, yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15953395 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 With friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5452685 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 Yes, oh yes, one or two of them as - three - well about four - four of us all told, boys, we were. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15953395 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 How about girl friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5452685 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 No, didn't used to bother a lot about them really.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15953395 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 Did you bring your friends home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5452685 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 Yes, oh yes, they've all been in our place there, yes, and I've been in theirs of course. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15953395 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 Did you have to be home by a certain time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5452685 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 Well they liked us to be, yes, we mainly always was really. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15953395 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 About what time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5452685 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 Oh anything - nine, half past nine, something like that, yes. Of course we was early morning people you see, yes. Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15953395 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 What year were you married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5452685 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 Oh what was it, 1916, during the war. Mm, 1916.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15953395 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 How long had you known your wife?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5452685 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 Oh - I used to chase here with a stick. Yes, used to chase her with a stick, I don't remember that though, but that
 was when we were school kids.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15953395 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 So you met at school did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5452685 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 
No, no, no, she used to go to - Christchurch School, I used to go to Dunstable Road. But I was born at the bakers business at 1 Salisbury Road, she was born at 9 Salisbury Road, see, o
h yes, only a day - just a door or two along you see. Well of course as kids we used to play you know but - I know her mother and my mother said you know I had a stick there, you know, we do with playing and - chasing them around like you know how we used
 to play - all sorts of games and that - round heads and suchlike, hide and seek and all that you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15953395 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 Was she the same age as you?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5452685 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 Yes, month difference, that's all, yes, was only a month in it, yes, mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15953395 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 Do you remember the first time you noticed her?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5452685 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 
Well - oh yes, oh that was - what - I know they moved - they had moved - they moved I think two different times they moved down to Hillside Road, and then they moved down into Belmont Road, they was in Belmonth Road along the Darrow Roa
d there really, but - lower - lower down Dumphrey Street - see - we was on the corner of - Salisbury Road and Dumphrey Street, and it was - quite a square there was one - two, three, four, five roads all run into this - centre with a big lamp right in the
 
centre you know, that's where we use to play round this old lamp you know, chase and race off up the different roads when we was hide and seek and that, and - but anyhow lower down - lower down - Dumphrey Street was Clarks, a big hat manufacturers. And of
 
course she was machinist there, and - she used to come - from Belmont Road which was in the Darrow Road well then the Peer Road and by the shop on the other side of the road you know, well of course Barrows shop was there, the grocers and go on down and t
hen down - down to the works you see and - well it was more or less then - I know I - well you can't definitely - state really but -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15953395 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 You used to see her go by?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5452685 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 Yes, we used to see her go by and perhaps I would be out just loading up the van or an
ything like that you know and then - we sort of started, you know, smiling and then - I know - then we had a chat and one thing and another and yes, and - and - then - there was one day - when her mother come along with her, and she was - apparently I thi
n
k was going down the town shopping but she walked along with her and - and I was out there un - unloading the van up you see and - she smiled across, so did the mother, of course I mean I knew the mother you see and knew 'em when they was living next to -
 
just at number nine and - but hadn't seen 'em like for all this time, not the mother and that. And - I went over and - chatted with 'em for a few minutes you see, then you - and then it was her really that first said about - do you remember chasing her - 
her - the girls around with this stick? Chase them round with a stick? No. Well you - you used to you know when - when we were - when we - when we - before we went. I said, I don't know, not so bad as all that. Oh you did. And - and - well there it was.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15953395 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 How old would you be now then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5452685 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 Pardon?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15953395 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 How old would you be when you met her again?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5452685 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 
Then? Oh round about - oh, what - oh it was up - 'course - that was like towards - well I don't know when it'd actually really be. Yes, about - about 191
0 I should think. Ten and eleven, something like that. Of course we was married in 1916. Her father and her brother both worked at Lyes, you know the bleachers and dyers, well you wouldn't know them, they was trem - terrific firm that. Bleachers and Dyers
. Always remember old dad used to say oh well of course we dyed to live and lived to dye, always remember him saying that, yes. Yes. Bleachers and dyers.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15953395 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 Can you remember the first time she took you home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5452685 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 Well I don't know about the first time, 
yes, well - it was quite early on and then she came - used to come up to our place, well of course it was mainly - mainly we used to have the old sing-songs round the table - round the piano Sunday evenings you see, 'cos she was in the choir at Waller Str
e
et, Wesleyan church, I was in the choir at Chapel Street, and - and that was it you see and then of course my brother as I say, he was a good pianist he was, he really went up and passed several exams up there at the London Academy for - pianist you know.
 Well I believe I told you that he was organist down here at the old church and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15953395 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 Did your wife have a good voice?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5452685 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 Yes, quite a good voice, oh yes, quite a good voice, soprano voice, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15953395 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 Can you remember the first time you went as her boyfriend, they realized you were getting together?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5452685 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 
Well, yes, I think - the first walk - the first walk we ever had? I - we - always remember that, was - we went right up the Farley Hill, do you know Stockwood Park, we went right through Stockwood Park, 
you know, there was a pathway right through the park, come out at the bottom lodge, 'cos see I was all familiar with that 'cos that - that was the round - that was the round I used to do Saturday afternoons when I went to school, through - through there I
 
mean because it wouldn't have mattered if any the Crawley's or anything had been about there you know, I should have waved to 'em, they'd have known me. And then when we come out - at the bottom lodge, then we walked right round like the outskirts, like o
n the Luton Caddington Road, see, and then back }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10505068\charrsid11272464 up to}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464  Farley Hill and come back down Farley Hill you see. Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15953395 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 And that was your first walk?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5452685 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 Yes, yes, was the very first walk we done, yes, I can remember.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15953395 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 What sort of home did she have, was it the same as yours?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5452685 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 
Oh quite nice home, yes, oh her mother was one of these - oh - oh look at that, hair there you know, must take that off. Yes, oh yes, quite - oh nice and spick and span like you know really, yes, oh yes, yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15953395 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 Did you get on well with her father?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5452685 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 Oh yes, yes, very well, oh Lor' yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15953395 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 They approved of you did they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5452685 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 
Yes, oh yes, yes, he used to - he always used to go up to King Street Brotherhood, you know, on the Sunday afternoon, but - main - mainly in th
e evenings and that he'd attend down Waller Street. They - they - you'd classify them as Waller Street - you know, Wesleyan people really, but he - I know he used to like the - the old Brotherhood up at King Street, 'cos I know he go on to me one day, wha
t
 about coming up there and singing, you know, and - I went up there and give 'em a couple of solos, I - I used to go all round there, I've been every church, every chapel in Luton singing. Yes, used to you know - they nearly always had a soloist at all th
o
se brotherhood meetings all those times ago. Fred, her brother - he - he - he - he never used to attend really, although quite - he was quite nice, quite a good chap, he was always out for a bit of fun and - always remember him saying about - always remem
b
er him saying on one occasion, of course it was always the PSA you know, Pleasant Sunday Afternoon, the Brotherhood was, he said, you know, he said, they've got hold of that wrong you know. I said, what? He said, that PSA, that don't mean Pleasant Sunday 
a
fternoon. Well, I said, what does it mean? Well he said, don't you know? I said, no. It means Please Stop Away. Yes. But still he's quite nice chap really. He worked at Lyesoh for years and years until lyes finished, and then he went into - to Alders, the
 opticians, he was their sort of receptionist then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15953395 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 Did she have any other brothers and sisters?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5452685 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 No. No. Fred was the only brother. And one sister, auntie Maude.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15953395 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 You got on well with them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5452685 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 Oh yes, got on well with them, yes, mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15953395 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 When you were recognised as her boyfriend were you treated as one of the family or always as a guest in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5452685 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 Oh more like one of the family like really, yes, oh yes, they was - they was - Maude's husband like - that was really - oh no, yes, they
'd just got married they had. He was a - he was an engineer he was, he was apprenticed at Hayward Tylers. Don't know if you've heard of Hayward Tylers, the big people here, well he was apprenticed there then soon as he came out of his apprenticeship - he 
w
ent to Coventry. But he was only Coventry about five or six weeks, he couldn't stick that and - and then - he - he heard of this job, a good job going down at Erith, you know, down in Kent there, at - at Vickers Armstrong, the big gun people and that. And
 
that's where he went you see and that's where they lived and of course we used to - visit them there, go down there you know. We used to go - perhaps - well we've been there by train. Got to St Pancras and then across the underground to - where the police
man did we used to go on the underground to, London Bridge, and then the train there - well of course ain}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10505068\charrsid11272464 \rquote }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 
t been on a train for donkey's years.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15953395 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 When you were courting did they let you talk together by yourselves and go off by yourselves?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5452685 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 Oh yes, yes, we did quite a bit, yes, oh yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15953395 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 If you were in the house in a room by yourselves would someone come in with you do you think?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5452685 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 Yes. No, no, no, no, no, didn't mind at all really, no, no. There was nearly always somebody or other like 
- Maude's husband and - the sister's husband, they'd be there and - well you was all like one little happy family as it were you see and - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15953395 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 How did you get on with your parents-in-law after you were married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5452685 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 Oh quite all right. Yes, oh pray 
yes, yes, quite all right right up until right up until you see the - 'til her - 'til her father died really. And then the mother then the mother came and lived with us you see, oh yes, she was -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15953395 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 So you saw a lot of them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5452685 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 Oh yes, she was passion
ately fond of gardening see, I've often said and I've said to people too, I reckon - I reckon she was the most wonderful woman really I think more or less ever lived really, because - you see - we had a hundred and eighty-five foot of garden then when we 
w
as down Oakley Road, and where - where - where she come to live with us there you see, we got a special little room there for her, we'd got six rooms and - and - she - she came to live with us and - I - in the springtime, in the springtime I used to - oh 
t
urn the garden all over, I'd turn it all over loose you know and I'd say, here you are grandma, it's all yours you see and - there'd be - used to leave her to it and I mean - she made us a couple of lovely rockeries and that, really I'd have never have th
ought of 'em you know, but she was a real proper green fingers, oh no doubt about that. And another}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10505068\charrsid11272464  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 
thing always stands out in my memory, you could just tell now how she was carried away with gardening. I came home - and - I'd been to Aylesbury this particu
lar day and it was about five o'clock, and I'd just arrived home, well - we'd got iron gates, then inside the iron gates you know we'd got wooden lattice gates, and then you see - at the - back, like - towards the back of the house was the garage you see.
 
And she couldn't see up the garden, 'til you got out the car and just went round the garage you see. Here was the back door here, and - I was opening the gates and the wife opened the back door, oh, she said, I was just going to open them. I would - I tho
ught you were a bit - perhaps be late - oh Lor' it's just started to rain, oh lumme, grandma's up the garden, you see. I sai}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10505068\charrsid11272464 d, I'll give her a shout. Right}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 . So - as I walked down to - open the garage doors and I just looked round and there she was on her ha
nds and knees. On her hands and knees up the garden - planting seeds you know. Oh nothing must be - I tell you that's how she was see. It had got to be bored, it had got to be perfectly straight, you know. Oy - come on in grandma. Hang on a minute. It's r
aining. She looked round, she - wells o it is, she said, oh well I'd better come on in then. See? And she - that's how she carried - that was how she was carried away with gardening.
