\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15953395 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 When they were both alive and getting on did you help them in their house with odd jobs at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5452685 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 Oh yes, we'd do anything like that, oh yes, if there was anything to do.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15953395 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 Did they think you were a good catch for their daughter?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5452685 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 Oh yes, I think they did, really. Well no, we were - we was all sort of one nice 
happy little family really, yes, I mean we - any of us, didn't matter what it was, we'd all turn in to do anything you know. Say they'd got a bit of a party on or anything of that, lumme, it was nothing for old George and I to wash up, we'd say right, mum
, you've done enough, you've prepared - always said, we'll do the washing up and leave 'em to it and they'd go off you see and go and sit in the front room and we'd - we used to have a joke doing that to each other.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15953395 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151623\charrsid11272464 What did you call them before you were married?
