No, no, he was quite a staunch teetotal - no, no, no George didn't either. No, he didn't either - well he was like me, he'd rather have a cup of tea any time. Alth
ough if I go out to a dinner, now we've got Dunstable Road Old Boy's dinner on - when's that, February the twenty-eighth, here you are, if you want a good evening out you want to come along to that, oh so you should, bring your husband along, that's the f
i
nest - the finest evening in Bedfordshire in the year, it is. That costs us what - that costs us seventy guineas for the cabaret show, we have the same cabaret show down from London. About a six course dinner. Dancing in between, there you are, yes, oh it
'
s a great night, up at the Halfway House, you know, the - hotel there on the Dun - yes, oh yes. Oh yes, bit place - we'll have people - do you know, honestly, I'm not kidding - I'm on the committee there, I've had people come up and pay me for next year. 
